24/04/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Czech Prime Minister Jiri Paroubek reaffirmed his country's strong support for Croatia's Euro-Atlantic bid, as he began an official two-day visit to Croatia on Sunday (23 April). Upon his arrival, Paroubek met with Croatian counterpart Ivo Sanader in Split, and then traveled Monday to Zagreb. A group of Czech business community members is accompanying Paroubek. (HRT - 23/04/06)
